Class SvgAnimationLanguage.Heap

java.lang.Object
  dxf2svg.sally.SvgAnimationLanguage.Heap
Direct Known Subclasses:
SvgAnimationLanguage.AnimationHeap, SvgAnimationLanguage.ModifyHeap
Enclosing class:
SvgAnimationLanguage
public abstract class SvgAnimationLanguage.Heap
extends java.lang.Object

This is the class that you must subclass to create a new heap. AnimationHeap and ModifyHeap both used this class as their template.

unpackSymbolTable

protected boolean unpackSymbolTable(SymbolTable sTable,
                                    java.util.Hashtable hTable)
This method will unpack a SymbolTable into the argument Hashtable. By passing the Hashtable as an argument we can allow for unpacking of symbol tables to any heap or multipule heaps.

Parameters:
sTable - to be unpacked
hTable - Destination to place the data from the symboltable.

getValue

protected java.lang.Object getValue(java.lang.String key)
This method will return the requested value. It should be noted that the return value is an Object but all stored values are Vectors of SvgAnimator or modifier objects.
